16/09/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- On Tuesday (16 September), Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg begins a two-day working visit to Croatia, where he will attend the opening ceremony of the Zagreb International Autumn Fair. Bulgaria is being granted the status of a partner country at the event. Saxe-Coburg will meet with Prime Minister Ivica Racan, Parliament Speaker Zlatko Tomcic and President Stipe Mesic.
Meanwhile, Bulgarian President Georgi Parvanov continues his tour of South Asia. In Singapore on Monday, he signed an agreement on reciprocal protection and promotion of investment. (Trud, 24 Chassa - 16/09/03; BTA, BNT, BNR - 15/09/03)
